DESCRIPTION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A set of fonts based on artwiz/artwiz-aleczapka with full ISO-8859-1 support

INSTALLATION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Do the following (example for gentoo):

	cd your_font_dir
	tar xvjf artwiz-latin1.tgz
	cd artwiz-latin1
	fc-cache -fv ./
	
	Add this path to your /etc/xorg.conf config
	FontPath "your_font_dir/artwiz-latin1"

	and fontconfig config file (eg. /etc/fonts/local.conf)
	<dir>your_font_dir/artwiz-latin1:unscaled</dir>

	restart X

Your installation may vary depending on your distro.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTES

	* kates-terminal, edges-terminal, lime-terminal, fkp-terminal, smoothansi-terminal

		These are the original artwiz-aleczapka's font's (without the -terminal suffix),
		i've included them in this package  so you can use Midnight Commander or another
		program that uses special terminal characters like, lines and corners.


